# GitLab Duo Custom Rules

Project: {{ project_name }}
Owner team: {{ owner_team }}

## General rules

- Plan before changing files.
- Keep diffs small and reviewable.
- Do not perform direct protected-branch updates.
- Do not expose secrets, masked variables, tokens, or private keys.
- Use Merge Request workflow for changes.
- Summarize changes in MR comments with validation evidence.

## DevSecOps rules

- Treat CI/CD configuration as security-sensitive.
- Review permissions and token scopes.
- Avoid privileged runners and containers unless justified.
- Prefer least privilege.
- Prefer pinned third-party dependencies/actions where applicable.
- Call out supply-chain and secret-exposure risks.

## Documentation rules

- Do not invent commands.
- Verify commands against repository files.
- Keep documentation task-oriented and copy-pasteable.
